      • formatTimeAsHHMM

        @Nonnull
public static String formatTimeAsHHMM(@Nullable
                                               Date date)
        General utility to format a time string as "HH:MM". Can be used in combination with randomEta to generate a nice ETA string. Example: String s = formatTimeAsHHMM(randomEta(new Date(), 60)).
        Parameters:
        date - Time to be formatted. If null, current time is used.
        Returns:
        Formatted time, as "HH:MM".

      • randomTime

        @Nonnull
public static Date randomTime(@Nullable
                                       Date date,
                                       int offset,
                                       int len)
        Generate a random time (for example, an ETA) from now, or any date/time.
        Parameters:
        date - Generate a time between 'date + offset' and 'date + offset + len'. If null, date is considered to be 'now'.
        offset - Minimum distance in minutes.
        len - Length of interval.
        Returns:
        Random time between [date + offset, date + offset + len].
